# **Part 2**

### **Describe a person who gave a clever solution to a problem.**

One person who immediately comes to mind is one of my classmates in university, who is really good at problem-solving, especially in programming-related tasks. I met him in my second year when we were taking a data structures course together, and we often worked on assignments as a team.

There was one particular situation that impressed me a lot. We were given a quite challenging programming assignment, and the problem was that our code kept running too slowly and couldn’t pass the time limit. At first, most of us tried to optimise the code by making small changes, like improving loops or reducing unnecessary calculations, but it didn’t really solve the issue.

Then this classmate came up with a completely different approach. Instead of just modifying the existing solution, he suggested changing the entire algorithm to a more efficient one. He carefully explained why the time complexity of our original method was too high, and then guided us step by step to implement a new solution. In the end, not only did the program run much faster, but it also became cleaner and easier to understand.

I think his solution was really clever because it wasn’t just about working harder, but about thinking in a smarter and more structured way. He was able to step back, analyse the problem from a deeper level, and find a fundamentally better approach. That experience really influenced me, and it made me realise the importance of choosing the right method instead of just focusing on details.

**中文翻译：**
我首先想到的是我大学的一位同学，他非常擅长解决问题，尤其是在编程方面。我是在大二上数据结构课的时候认识他的，我们经常一起做作业。

有一次让我印象特别深刻。我们有一个比较难的编程作业，问题是程序运行太慢，无法通过时间限制。刚开始我们都在做一些小优化，比如改循环、减少计算，但效果不明显。

后来这位同学提出了一个完全不同的思路。他没有继续在原来的代码上修改，而是建议换一种更高效的算法。他还解释了原来方法的时间复杂度为什么太高，并一步步带着我们实现新方案。最后程序不仅运行更快，而且结构更清晰。

我觉得这个解决方案很聪明，因为他不是更努力地改代码，而是从更高层去思考问题，找到本质更优的方法。这件事对我影响很大，让我意识到方法比细节更重要。

